## Testing plan

Gates that apply: `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`.

- `build`: solution builds with the nine new Optimization files registered, the ALGLIB `PackageReference` resolving, and `SynthesisFitPage.fs` compiling against the FuncUI DSL surface WITHOUT the clone dependency (§0 constraint 5; `update` contains no Avalonia type).
- `unit-tests`: `BerremanTests` runs `OptimizationTests.fs` (G.11). This slice ADDS passing tests to `BerremanTests`, so the `count_at_least` baseline rises; record the new `berreman_unit_tests` count in the state-of-the-world. The Wolfram R/T and Ψ/Δ cases (AC-G9), the bounded-fit case (AC-G3), and the needle-insertion case (AC-G6) run over the real solver path (no stub).
- `constructor-unit-tests`: the `OpticalConstructor.Tests` project still builds and passes; add (if desired) interface-boundary tests asserting no ALGLIB type crosses the G.1 boundary (AC-G1) and the `DesignParameter` fold round-trip (AC-G2). The gate MUST stay green.
- Emit the state-of-the-world file with the `gates:` YAML baseline block (record the NEW `berreman_unit_tests` count).

## Risks

- **High:** the ALGLIB NuGet `PackageReference` must resolve and link under .NET 10 / `x64` for the `build` and `unit-tests` gates to pass; the Wolfram-reference tests (AC-G9) require the real `minlm` path. If ALGLIB cannot be resolved in the environment, the round escalates rather than stubbing the forward model. Verify the package restores before relying on the end-to-end tests.
- **Medium:** `NelderMead` MUST NOT be bound to a spec-invented ALGLIB routine; it surfaces `Failed "simplex backend unresolved"` (G.2). A test asserting that behavior guards against accidental resolution.
- **Medium:** confidence-interval/correlation covariance (G.8) must route through `MathNetNumericsMath.fs:5`, NOT ALGLIB (§A.8); mixing the two violates the numerics boundary.

## Hand-off

State carried to later slices:
- The full `OpticalConstructor.Optimization` assembly exists: interface (`OptimizationInterface.fs`), sole ALGLIB adapter (`AlglibAdapter.fs`), design-variable mapping (`DesignParameters.fs`), merit editor (`MeritFunction.fs`), local refinement (`LocalRefinement.fs`), ellipsometry (`Ellipsometry.fs`), inverse fit (`InverseFit.fs`), fit-quality/`FitReport` (`FitQuality.fs`), synthesis (`Synthesis.fs`).
- `SynthesisFitPage.fs` exists; Part J §J.10 (slice 010) supplies the shared `JobRunner` that hosts the optimizer run with progress/cancel, and Part H (slice 008) supplies the `plotComparison`-backed overlay refresh.
- `FitReport` persists as a `.binz` fit-history sidecar via the Part A `Softellect.Sys.Core.serialize` seam; Part I (slice 009) provides `writeSidecar`/`readSidecar` and the `.gitignore` entry for `*.binz`.
- The `berreman_unit_tests` baseline rose this slice (new `OptimizationTests.fs`).

